<br>
 I then used my MS I pet(summoned until I got the one with the Fire pet DS.)  The MS pet is very impressive(hits for 32 not 34 like 2 of the focus pets.)  It seems to have just as many hit points as the Earth pet plus the added bonus of a nice DS.  It easily holds it's own against 2 mobs(guards in Highkeep) with 2 heals and a few nukes by me.  <br>
<br>
Should focus item pets be superior to the MS pets?  So far the MS I pet seems to be better than focus lvl 34 pets, at least in Highkeep. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dabrighter2>Dabrighter2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#333333>(1/17/03 11:06:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=939.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus items pets vs. MS pets</span><hr size=1> The MS I pet is like a cross of the Earth pet and the Fire Pet.  It has the Hit points of the Earth pet, but the better Damage Mitagation of the Fire Pet.  It also gets the Fire Pets Damage shield.  It doesn't cast a fire dd or a root, but meeles for more because it does not cast.  <br>
<br>
The biggest problem with the Earth pet is nearly everything hits if for full nearly everytime.  Great if you have a damage shield on it, but does not tank multilpe mobs well.  It also takes forever to heal.  At this level, the mana cost to resummon a new pet is a big burden so resummoning a full pet does not make a lot of sense, especially if you gave it any items.  <br>
<br>
The fire pet has better damage mitigation, but not nearly the hit points.  If just does not have the hit points to live long while be attacked by multiple mobs.  The fireshield really tears through mobs, but keeping the Fire pet alive when being attacked by mutliple mobs is challenging.  <br>
<br>
The MS pet has the best attributes of both pets without having that pets biggest weakness.  It is often the pet of choice when tanking multiple mobs at once.  It is a very useful pet during this level of spells.  <br>
<br>
Enjoy it advantages now.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=acidlarfleshburner>Acidlar Fleshburner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#333333>(1/18/03 12:59:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=939.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/hmain/Pics/Gifs/supe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus items pets vs. MS pets</span><hr size=1> I used MS2 over the level 51 earth when I had the time / malachite, to get a MS pet that would DS itself. <p><center><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378512"><IMG SRC="http://www.telusplanet.net/public/hmain/Pics/Sig/britsig.jpg" BORDER=0 ALT="Level 51 Mage"></A></center><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378512" style="text-decoration:none">
